def: Growth or development of new material; neoplasty.
One in whom the property of an estate is vested, subject to theestate of a life renter.I am fiar of the lands; she a life renter. Sir W. Scott.
Of or pertaining to the Brahmans or to their doctrines andworship.
To teach; to instruct.I . . . shall tutorize him some day. J. H. Newman.
The state or quality of being green; verdure. [R.]The greenth of summer. G. Eliot.
A monster capable of assuming a woman's form, who was said todevour human beings or suck their blood; a vampire; a sorceress; awith.
Perplexed by doubts originating in one's own mind.
Pertaining to the monks of St. Benedict, or St. Benet.
The structureless, protoplasmic tissue of the embryo; theprimitive basis of an organ yet unformed, from which it grows.
The act of legislating; preparation and enactment of laws; thelaws enacted.Pythagoras joined legislation to his philosophy. Lyttelton.
